title: Draw ideas from base scribble
summary:
Creative scribble - draw over doodle,

come with an original idea more than once.

train your mind to think 'out of the box'

Instructions:

1. Draw (as simple as possible) a basic scribble.
Preferably, a single stroked, meaningless 'something', which doesn't resembles anything.

2. confirm done.

3. Now, add as few as possible strokes and make it into something meaningful

4. confirm done( or confirm 'done plus' : to express another idea over the same basic scribble)

5. go over to the gallery and respect your creative mind

* Better to play with friends (by solving the same original doodle/Scribble)
